Press Releases.Title: 12 New Cases of Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 4 October 2020, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed an additional 12 cases of COVID-19 infection in Singapore. Based on our investigations so far, there are 2 cases in the community, both of whom are Work Pass holders. 

2.       There are 6 imported cases, who had all been placed on Stay-Home Notice upon arrival in Singapore.  

3.       We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight. 


MINISTRY OF HEALTH
4 OCTOBER 2020
